text: Ekaterina Zelentsova (born 29 January 1991) is a Russian water polo player. She was a member of the Russian women's national water polo team. She played in the 2009 Summer Universiade, 2013 Summer Universiade, and 2013 World Aquatics Championships. == References == Category:1991 births Category:Living people Category:Russian water polo players
